dcterms:description: Yeast data sets annotating yeast genome from different aspects, each with hierarchical-structured labels in the Functional Catalogue (FunCat). Each yeast genome can be associated with multiple functionalities, with an average of 8.8 labels per instance.

dcterms:description: Medical data sets obtained from an online medical consultation website where patients post healthcare-related questions and multiple medical professionals provide suggestions or general advice as answers. The disease label hierarchy is organized in an anatomical structure.
